een readers’ L1 and L2 is reflected in systematic differences between L1 speakers of Persian and French in their L2 lexical inferencing. Implications are drawn for L2 instruction at advanced levels.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aInference. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aVocabularyxStudy and teaching. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aL1 transfer.  aL2 instruction.  aL2 reading.  aLexical Inferencing.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  acrosslinguistic influence.  atransfer in language learning.  avocab learning.  avocabulary learning.1 aHaastrup, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParibakht, T. Sima, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769224540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847692245423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847692245/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK